      </p>

      <h3>Who this course is for</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Students in law, business, or engineering who want to understand IP basics.</li>
        <li>Entrepreneurs and startups looking to protect their ideas and innovations.</li>
        <li>Professionals in R&D, design, or product management roles.</li>
        <li>Anyone interested in learning about global IP rights and enforcement.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>What you'll learn in this course:</h3>
      <ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
        <li>Introduction to Intellectual Property Rights and their importance.</li>
        <li>Patents: filing, duration, and case studies of patent disputes.</li>
        <li>Trademarks and branding strategies for businesses.</li>
        <li>Copyrights in creative industries: music, films, books, and software.</li>
        <li>Trade secrets and industrial designs.</li>
        <li>International IP laws: WIPO, TRIPS Agreement, and regional differences.</li>
      </ul>
